Text.Value: I'm looking into the death of a waveservant - do you know anything about it?
Such things are the work of servants. Do I look like a servant?
Something else you want to know now, eh?
Don't really have any to spare. Maybe if I tried pissing on it...?
Well, you clearly ain't, or you'd have said something useful.
The boat's fine, but the nets are in tatters.

EditorData.NodeContext: Irritated by the state of the nets

Text.Value: Oil? This isn't black blood?
Now did you want something or do you just have an interest in fishing vessels?

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly annoyed but also slightly inquisitive

Text.Value: Why are there so many dead fish floating in the harbour?
Course not! You've been talking to that lot from the Water Queen's House, haven't you?
Have you tried vinegar?
Kind of looked like it might have been heading towards that building across the channel, actually.
Leave.
Too bad we can't sell 'em - bloody waste, if you ask me.
Don't suppose you've got any experience getting oil out of sealed wood?
Is your boat all right?
Oh, sure. In fact, we fished her out of the water.
What happened to her body?
Where did all this stuff come from anyway?
Buggered if I know. Might be something to do with all that oil in the water.
Then all of a sudden my net starts dragging and there's a bloody waveservant all twisted up in it!
We both saw some sort of wake moving towards the docks when we picked her up - but there weren't any other boats around.
We took her back to the docks to try and help her but she was already dead.
Leave.
They took her back to the temple. Can hear their bloody caterwauling from here.
Maybe it was something big moving underwater? I dunno - it was weird, whatever it was.
The other waveservants came to get it. Her. Sorry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Catching himself as he realise this might sound insensitive

Text.Value: Hells, it's everywhere still!
Me and Fleer here were out on the water casting our nets, expecting to find the usual crop of halibut.
Did you see anything else unusual?
Ugh, don't have time for all this scrubbing when there's fish to catch.
Need to deal with all this oil before we can fix them, though.
I'm sure it'll come out eventually.

Synopsis: The fisher brother explains where they found the injured waveservant and that they don't know what hurt her. He reveals that when they found her, they saw a turbolence going towards the docks and that a Grey Waver was pointing and shouting at it.
